{"questionId":"27747038","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A particle moves in a straight line such that its velocity, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi>ms</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>, at time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>&nbsp;seconds is given by</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The particle’s acceleration is zero at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>T</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This sample question was produced by experienced DP mathematics senior examiners to aid teachers in preparing for external assessment in the new MAA course. There may be minor differences in formatting compared to formal exam papers.</p>\n<p>attempts either graphical or symbolic means to find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>&nbsp;when&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>465</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[2 marks]</strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27747038","referenceCode":"EXN.2.SL.TZ0.3a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of T.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.9—Kinematics problems"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}